stylometry: The group project we did was the pizza shop. We were trying to determine how many delivery drivers we needed to have during the busiest time of day. The three hour time spot has us making 50 pizzas to meet the demand and delivering all 50. This was determined by using the @RISK program which gave us the 50 demand of pizzas, we then needed to determine how many drivers it would take to deliver all 50 pizzas in a timely manner. The way we did this was by setting a price per driver and then allowing the @RISK to give us a solution based on the cost of having each driver for that three hours and how many we would need to deliver all 50 pizzas in a timely manner. We missed one vital step that we needed to have, which was how long it takes a driver to deliver a pizza. if we would have taken that into consideration we would have had a better answer than what we found.
